sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User<br/>kubectl/oc
    participant API as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>443→9443/TCP mTLS
    participant DSCCtrl as DSC Controller<br/>Leader Elected
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant CompOp as Component Operator<br/>e.g., KServe

    Note over User,CompOp: Flow 1: User Creates DataScienceCluster

    User->>API: POST DataScienceCluster CR<br/>Auth: User credentials
    API->>Webhook: Validate/Mutate DSC<br/>mTLS (API server cert)
    Webhook-->>API: Validation passed<br/>Defaults applied
    API-->>User: CR created

    Note over API,DSCCtrl: Operator Watch Triggers

    API->>DSCCtrl: Watch event<br/>DSC created

    Note over DSCCtrl,K8sAPI: Flow 2: Operator Reconciles Components

    DSCCtrl->>K8sAPI: GET DataScienceCluster<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>DSCCtrl: DSC spec

    DSCCtrl->>K8sAPI: CREATE Namespace<br/>redhat-ods-applications
    DSCCtrl->>K8sAPI: CREATE Deployment<br/>odh-dashboard
    DSCCtrl->>K8sAPI: CREATE Subscription<br/>kserve-operator (OLM)
    DSCCtrl->>K8sAPI: CREATE ConfigMap<br/>component configs
    DSCCtrl->>K8sAPI: CREATE ServiceMonitor<br/>monitoring config

    K8sAPI-->>DSCCtrl: Resources created

    DSCCtrl->>K8sAPI: UPDATE DSC status<br/>Phase: Ready

    Note over CompOp: Component Operator Deploys
    CompOp->>K8sAPI: Deploy component resources

    Note over User,CompOp: Flow 3: Monitoring Scrapes Metrics

    participant Prom as Prometheus
    participant AuthProxy as Auth Proxy<br/>kube-rbac-proxy
    participant MetricsEP as Metrics Endpoint<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Prom->>AuthProxy: GET /metrics<br/>8443/TCP<br/>Bearer token
    AuthProxy->>API: TokenReview<br/>Validate ServiceAccount
    API-->>AuthProxy: Token valid
    AuthProxy->>MetricsEP: Forward request<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    MetricsEP-->>AuthProxy: Prometheus metrics
    AuthProxy-->>Prom: Metrics response
